1 (ii) The State Library Agency;
2 (iii) The Governor’s Office of the Deaf and Hard of Hearing;
3 (iv) Statewide deaf and hard of hearing organizations; and
4 (v) Other organizations as agreed on by the Governor’s Office of the
5 Deaf and Hard of Hearing and the State Library Agency; and
6 (8) Establish a Deaf Culture Digital Library “Friends of the Library” group
7 composed of individuals who are strongly committed, well–positioned, and able to promote
8 community involvement, advocacy, and funding for the Deaf Culture Digital Library.
9 (c) The lead employee or coordinator who manages the Deaf Culture Digital
10 Library shall be:
11 (1) A deaf or hard of hearing individual; and
12 (2) Knowledgeable and experienced concerning issues affecting deaf and
13 hard of hearing individuals.
14 (D) FOR FISCAL YEAR 2026 AND EACH FISCAL YEAR THEREAFTER, THE
15 GOVERNOR SHALL INCLUDE IN THE ANNUAL BUDGET BILL AN APPROPRIATION OF
16 $450,000 TO THE DEAF CULTURE DIGITAL LIBRARY.
17 (E) THE DEAF CULTURE DIGITAL LIBRARY SHALL SUBMIT ITS ANNUAL
18 OPERATING BUDGET TO THE STATE LIBRARY AGENCY ON OR BEFORE JUNE 1 EACH
19 YEAR.
20 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
21 1, 2025.

